:"admitted"} or Acl{action:"blocked"} \n - `handle_incoming` (inbound Mention to hosted agent) → Msg (inbound) \n - `handle_incoming` (Status envelope) → Status (with dedup) \n - `handle_incoming` (Profile envelope) → Profile (first-seen dedup) \n - `handle_incoming` (Presence envelope, first-seen) → Join (via peer_sessions map) \n - `spawn_pruner` (sessions dropped from DB) → Leave \n  \n JOIN/LEAVE + SUPPRESSION \n  \n Join/Leave have no relay round-trip. An in-memory `peer_sessions: Mutex<HashMap<String, PeerTracked>>` on DaemonState tracks `{first_seen, project, slug, host}` keyed by session_id. When a Presence envelope arrives: if session_id is not in the map, emit Join and insert; subsequent beats are silent. When the pruner sweeps, it calls `list_peer_sessions(None, before)` to get the still-alive set after the DB prune, then emits Leave for every session that was in the map but is not in the post-prune live set, removing them from the map. \n  \n Profile dedup: `seen_profiles: Mutex<HashSet<String>>` — first pubkey occurrence emits Profile, repeats are dropped. \n Status dedup: `last_status: Mutex<HashMap<(String,String),String>>` keyed by (pubkey, project) — only emits when the status string differs from the last-seen value. \n  \n NEW CLI FLAGS (17 total on `tail` subcommand) \n  \n | Flag | Effect | \n |------|--------| \n | `--project <slug>` | scope to one project | \n | `--agent <slug>` | filter by agent | \n | `--host <host>` | filter by host | \n | `--since <spec>` | backfill start (unix ts or 1h/30m/2d/60s) | \n | `--backfill <n>` | limit backfill messages (default 50) | \n | `--only <cat,...>` | whitelist categories | \n | `--exclude <cat,...>` | blacklist categories | \n | `--include <cat,...>` | add back excluded | \n | `--all` | min_tier = noise (everything) | \n | `--compact` | no project/host annotations | \n | `--relative` | relative timestamps | \n | `--no-emoji` | ASCII fallbacks | \n | `--no-color` | strip ANSI (also respects NO_COLOR env) | \n | `--json` | NDJSON output | \n | `--no-follow` | exit after backfill + 500ms | \n | `--live` | reserved (prints "not yet implemented") | \n  \n TESTS ADDED / UPDATED \n  \n 14 new unit tests in `cli.rs::tail_render_tests`: \n  \n - `test_render_msg_outbound`, `test_render_msg_inbound` — Msg variant with/without emoji \n - `test_render_turn_working`, `test_render_turn_idle` — Turn state transitions \n - `test_render_join`, `test_render_leave` — Join/Leave with session short codes \n - `test_render_acl_pending`, `test_render_acl_action` — Acl admitted/blocked \n - `test_render_sess_start`, `test_render_sess_end` — own session lifecycle \n - `test_parse_since_unix`, `test_parse_since_duration_h`, `test_parse_since_duration_m`, `test_parse_since_duration_d` — parse_since edge cases \n  \n Unit tests in `tail_event.rs`: tier ordering, category names, serde roundtrip. \n  \n CAPTURED LIVE DEMO OUTPUT \n  \n ``` \n ===== LIVE TAIL ===== \n 18:43:17  turn   claude@tmp[c131aa]  > started working \n 18:43:17  msg    claude@tmp[c131aa]  -> codex[3178f1] #thr-18b7 "can you review the tail v2 codec seam refactor?" \n 18:43:17  sync   claude → 38521b5a #thr-18b7  [ok] delivered \n 18:43:17  msg    codex@tmp[3178f1]  -> claude[c131aa] #thr-18b7 "looks good - one nit: doc the seam test" \n 18:43:17  sync   codex → db6202dc #thr-18b7  [ok] delivered \n 18:43:17  turn   claude@tmp[c131aa]  || idle (0s) \n ``` \n  \n FULL LADDER SUMMARY \n  \n | Suite | Passed | Failed | Warnings | \n |-------|--------|--------|----------| \n | lib (unit) | 135 | 0 | 0 | \n | daemon_integration | 15 | 0 | | \n | daemon_mechanics | 4 | 0 | | \n | e2e_transport | 1 | 0 | | \n | relay_probe | 0 (2 ignored — require live relay) | 0 | | \n  \n Total: 155 tests pass, 0 fail, 0 warnings. Commit: `e4086e1`. \n  \n Assistant: The `tail` v2 Engineer committed (`e4086e1`) — 155 tests green, 0 warnings, and the live demo shows the new readable format. Let me verify the join and then build the `propose` sub