36cc4-9 | 2026-06-12T20:13:05Z | session:36cc4546-228e-4d07-a1a8-9d0cd7cd5a6c | ### **Current Status: Fully Implemented & Tested** ✓ \n  \n The codec integration is **complete and working** as of 2026-06-09. All 19 codec unit tests pass, and codec functionality has been verified in live e2e demos on `relay.tenex.chat`. [...] **The codec seam** (`src/codec/mod.rs`) defines a `Codec` trait with four verbs: \n  \n | Verb | Purpose | \n |------|---------| \n | `name()` | Stable wire-shape identifier (`"kind1"` for M1) | \n | `encode()` | DomainEvent → unsigned EventBuilder | \n | `decode()` | nostr Event → DomainEvent (or None) | \n | `filters()` | SubScope → relay filter subscriptions | [...] **Domain layer is transport-agnostic.** `src/domain.rs` names no Nostr kind, tag, or relay concept—only five nouns (Profile, Presence, Activity, Status, Mention) that any codec must implement. [...] **Wire mapping** (`src/codec/kind1.rs`): \n - **Profile** → kind:0, content `{"name": slug}`, `["host", host]`, `["p", owner]…` \n - **Presence** → kind:30315 (NIP-38), `["d", "tenex-edge-presence:<session>"]`, `["h", project]`, `["session-id", id]`, `["agent", pk, slug]`, `["p", audience]…` \n - **Activity** → kind:1, `["h", project]`, `["agent", pk, slug]` \n - **Status** → kind:30315, `["h", project]`, `["d", project]`, `["agent", pk, slug]` \n - **Mention** → kind:1, `["p", to_pubkey]`, `["h", project]`, `["agent", pk, slug]`; Activity/Mention both kind:1 — disambiguated on decode by presence of `p` tag. [...] The **Codec trait is currently coupled to Nostr** (`nostr_sdk` types in signatures). The documentation flags this as a **deliberate seam boundary** that must be elevated for future transport swaps: \n  \n > "To support any transport, the swap seam should be elevated to a `Fabric` trait that takes abstract `DomainEvent` and `SubScope` types, making `encode`/`decode`/`filters` private implementation details of a `NostrFabric`." [...] - `filters` verb bakes in relay REQ semantic